    {
      "id": "reflection",
      "label": "Reflection",
      "indexLabel": "Reflections",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "section-label",
          "label": "Reflection",
          "uid": "bfjl6a47n"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "body": "My role shifted across this project. I started in the thinking phase direction, system, flow architecture. I ended up sitting with developers daily, going screen by screen, making sure what shipped matched what was designed.",
          "uid": "bbvh6dvm0"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "body": "The pixel-perfect phase isn't vanity. When you're rebuilding trust in a product people have written off, every rough edge is a reason to leave again.",
          "uid": "b2wrj69ab"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "body": "The hardest call wasn't a design decision. It was arguing for a focused launch pushing back on the feature list, convincing stakeholders that a wallet which earns one user's trust completely is worth more than one that half-impresses everyone. That's the one I'm most proud of.",
          "uid": "bz221xgq4"
        },
        {
